306.8	Transmission_Control_Protocol	Transmission Control Protocol	TCP protocol operations may be divided into three phases. Connections must be properly established in a multi-step handshake process before entering the data transfer phase. After data transmission is completed, the connection termination closes established virtual circuits and releases all allocated resources.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f6/Tcp_state_diagram_fixed_new.svg/250px-Tcp_state_diagram_fixed_new.svg.png
